{"questionId":"33291988","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtext>AB</mtext></mfenced></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>A</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math>, the midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtext>BC</mtext></mfenced></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>B</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math>, the midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtext>CD</mtext></mfenced></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>C</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math> and the midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtext>DA</mtext></mfenced></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>D</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Consider the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>w</mi><mi>p</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Four of the roots of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>w</mi><mi>p</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi></msup></math> are represented by the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>A</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>B</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>C</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>D</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the least possible value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and the corresponding value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arg</mtext><mo> </mo><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>8</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mtext>AA</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><mtext>=</mtext><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mtext>OA</mtext><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∴</mo><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo> </mo><mi>cis</mi><mo> </mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>considers when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arg</mtext><mo> </mo><mtext> </mtext><mfenced><msup><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>p</mi></msup></mfenced><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math> (multiple of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33291988","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.12e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the least possible value of p and the corresponding value of q.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Properties of discrete and continuous random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}